race.comment: BAND OF BROTHERS (4) goes well for hoop Mallyon who has a win and two placings from just three steers and has been racing very consistently this time in work. Only needs some luck navigating from the sticky draw to be playing a major role in the outcome. ESJAY (13) is yet to miss a drum in four starts over this course and distance and gets in on the minimum weight here. Has to be included. MICKEY'S MEDAL (6) brings Sydney formlines to the table and will be ready to peak now fourth run back from the break. Top-three credentials. MISTER BIANCO (7) is a two-time winner over this seven furlong journey, draws low and gets 3kg weight relief with the claim. Ticks a few boxes. OUR MAGNUS (9) is usually thereabouts and is one for the multiples.
